ABC managing director Mark Scott shook off the viral campaign on Thursday issuing a tweet saying 'It's gonna be alright @triplej' about the trending hashtag. 

It kicked off after Joe McKenzie tweeted Scott about the omission of Swift's hit from the Triple J's Hottest 100 voting list.

'Triple J is refusing to let me vote for Taylor Swift in the Hottest 100 I personally blame @mcscott [Scott's Twitter handle],' he wrote.

To which, Scott replied: 'Shake it off Joe.'

Voting for the Hottest 100 closes on Sunday and the results will be aired on Australia Day. 

Triple J - which is controlled by the ABC - provides 2,000 songs played on the radio station during the year for people to choose from in their votes. 

But the system allows voter to manually enter their selections, which some decided to take advantage of. 

